{{Infobox coat of arms |name = Emblem of His Majesty the Emperor of Ashanti |image = Ashanti Emblem.png |image_width = 200 |middle = |middle_width = |middle_caption = |lesser = |lesser_width = |lesser_caption = |armiger = {{flag|Ashanti}} |year_adopted = December 30, 1701 |crest = [[Porcupine]] |torse = |shield = Remarkably threatening looking red "Porcupine", displaying an inbuilt arsenal of sharp spikes for use when attacked by an enemy. |supporters = |compartment = |motto = "Kum apem a, apem beba" (Kill a thousand, a thousand will come) |orders = |other_elements = |earlier_versions = |use = }} The '''Emblem of His Majesty the Emperor of Ashanti''' (or [[National emblem|National Emblem]] of '''[[Ashanti Region|Ashanti]]''') is the [[national emblem]] of the [[Ashanti Region|Ashanti nation]], adopted by Ashanti's emperor [[Asantehene]] [[Osei Kofi Tutu I|Osei Tutu I]] in 1701, and is based on the [[Porcupine]], which has been the Ashanti national animal since 1701 the early-eighteenth century [[Anno Domini|AD]].<ref name="Ashanti Gold Weights"/><ref name="The porcupine fights from all angles"/><ref name="Ashanti Animal Porcupine"/>
==Emblem origin== The Porcupine in the Asante national emblem was used by the emperor [[Asantehene]] of [[Asante Region|Asante]] in taking the oath of office to Asante in the late 17th century AD.<ref name="Ashanti Gold Weights"/><ref name="The porcupine fights from all angles"/> The Porcupine represents the designated [[national animal]] of Ashanti.<ref name="Ashanti Gold Weights"/><ref name="The porcupine fights from all angles"/> The national emblem of Ashanti was created by emperor Asantehene [[Nana (title)|Nana]] [[Osei Kofi Tutu I]] ([[Reign|r]]. 1695 – 1717).<ref name="Ashanti Gold Weights"/><ref name="The porcupine fights from all angles"/><ref name="Ashanti Animal Porcupine"/>
==Emblem description== The national emblem of [[Ashanti Region|Ashanti]] is surmounted by a red [[Porcupine]] (or [[Asante dialect|Ashanti]]: Kotoko) on a [[gold (color)|gold]] background symbolizing the soil [[gold|gold mineral]] wealth and [[gold bar]] wealth of [[Ashanti Region|Ashanti]]; the Porcupine has been the designated national animal of [[Ashanti Region|Ashanti]] since 1701 into the present 21st century representing the [[Ashanti people]] proverb "The porcupine fights from all angles" and the [[Ashanti people]] readiness of the [[Ashanti Region|Ashanti nation]] to wage war on its enemies and the [[Ashanti Region|Ashanti nation]] motto "Kum apem a, apem beba" (Kill a thousand, a thousand will come) in reference to the Porcupine's quills as symbols of [[Ashanti people|Ashanti]] warriors, is still quoted.<ref name="Ashanti Gold Weights">{{cite web|url=http://www.arts-are-essential.org/saproject06/lesson_plans/lp_elem_AshantiGold.pdf|title=Ashanti Gold Weights|type=PDF|pages= 3–4|work=arts-are-essential.org}}</ref><ref name="The porcupine fights from all angles">{{cite web|url=http://www.aluka.org/stable/10.5555/al.ch.document.bfacp1b10209|title=Ashanti carving representing the proverb "The porcupine fights from all angles" A symbol of the Ashanti kingdom"|work=aluka.org}}</ref><ref name="Ashanti Animal Porcupine">{{cite web|url=https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=9kAjZbZRDKoC&pg=PT20&redir_esc=y#v=onepage&q&f=false|title=Ashanti Animal Porcupine|author=Citlalli López Binnqüist, Patricia Shanley| work=Google Books}}</ref>
